               <p><persName>Ruth</persName> (maiden name unknown) was born in <placeName>Woolley,
                     Yorkshire</placeName>, converted in <placeName>York</placeName> in <date
                     when="1752">1752</date>, married in <date when="1753">1753</date>, and claimed
                  entire sanctification in <date when="1757">1757</date>. She and <persName><ptr
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> carried on extensive
                  correspondence between <date from="1759" to="1762">1759 and 1762</date>, though
                  only <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>&apos;s published
                  transcriptions of her letters survive. See &apos;A Short Account of <persName>Ruth
                     Hall</persName>&apos;, <hi rend="italic">AM</hi> 4 (<date when="1781"
                     >1781</date>): 477–80; and Lyth, <hi rend="italic">Methodism in York</hi>, 64,
